fields.value: Census of Agriculture, 1982 Final County File

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This file contains data from the 1982 census with comparable data for selected items from the 1978 census. Data are presented for all farms and selected data are presented for farms with sales of $10,000 or more. Data include number of farms, land in farms, major uses of farmland, farm size and irrigation of farmland, tenure and characteristics of the operator, farms by type of organization, selected production expenses, agricultural chemicals used, value of machinery and equipment, value of agricultural products sold, and farm-related income. Data also are included on inventories and sales of livestock and poultry and crops harvested. Data items are standard but data availability for selected crops varies by State according to the crops' relative importance. Also, the variable tables for minor crops and livestock are standard, but data may not be available for every State.

Data are available for each State and all counties.

fields.value: Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: The universe is all farms. A farm is defined as any place from which $1,000 or more of agricultural products were sold, or normally would have been sold, during the census year.;Type: ODUM:ACCESS.CATEGORY Notes: I;
